data.title: "John Cotton Dana: An Address by Frank Kingdon", 1935
data.text:
From the Sub-Series:

This subseries consists of subject files filed alphabetically, usually by subject, genre, or organization name. Subjects include music, theater, fine arts, poetry, photography, film, and cultural events (including library, museum, history, African-American heritage events). Material includes calendars created by Kukla, playbills, pamphlets, fliers, and booklets, documenting arts and culture in New Jersey. Research materials for Kukla’s gospel calendar are filed under “Gospel Calendar” (See also: Series 1A and Series 8, Box OV-1, Folder 6). Also of note, an extensive collection of playbills from New Jersey theaters and information on historical celebrations of Black History Month and Martin Luther King Day in the Newark area.
